episode_id.description:
User Guidance: Use this field to link the EPISODE_EVENT record to its EPISODE.

ETL Conventions: Put the EPISODE_ID that subsumes the EPISODE_EVENT record here.

event_id.description:
User Guidance: This field is the primary key of the linked record in the database. For example, if the Episode Event is a Condition Occurrence, then the CONDITION_OCCURRENCE_ID of the linked record goes in this field.

ETL Conventions: Put the primary key of the linked record here.

episode_event_field_concept_id.description:
User Guidance: This field is the CONCEPT_ID that identifies which table the primary key of the linked record came from.

ETL Conventions: Put the CONCEPT_ID that identifies which table and field the EVENT_ID came from. [Accepted Concepts](https://athena.ohdsi.org/search-terms/terms?vocabulary=CDM&conceptClass=Field&page=1&pageSize=15&query=)
